post_text:
Driving away from my child after school drop-off was the hardest thing.

There are so many bad stories in the news...

Was my child really safe? What could I do to be sure?

Another parent recommended Pawnee Independent School District, and now I know why.

From the moment we walked through the door, we both felt safe and secure.

Their concern for safety is evident in something as simple as the new parking layout.

Nothing compares to knowing that my child is well looked after and happy at school.

Find peace-of-mind knowing your child is safe at Pawnee Independent School District.

Much of childhood is, ‚ÄúWait till you‚Äôre older.‚Äù

At Pawnee Early Learning Academy, learning starts NOW!

Three and four-year-olds in the right environment grow super-brains!

Specially trained teachers will get to know children and personalize learning.

Your child will build an early academic foundation through directed play.

Small classes let learners develop trust in their teachers and make learning safe and FUN!

Your little one will come home bursting with new ideas from exploring a diverse classroom.

At Pawnee Early Learning Academy, three and four-year-olds are our favorite starting place!

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

We will post any additional information on our website and Facebook page as it becomes available.

Dear Pawnee ISD Family,
Pawnee ISD is closely monitoring the spread of COVID-19 in our state while our district is on its regularly scheduled Spring Break. All school-related activities, including UIL athletic games and practices have been cancelled until March 29th. A decision on our schools and office days and times of operations will be made and released by the end of business, Wednesday.

To the best of our ability, information regarding alternative methods of instruction and student access to meals will be included with this release. Administrators are working closely with local officials to be certain that our community's health and well being remains priority one.

Please continue to check our social media accounts for updates on the situation. Thank you for doing your part as we work through these uncertain times together.

Sincerely,
Michelle Hartmann
Superintendent

The Coastal Bend Food Band along with Pawnee United Methodist and Pawnee ISD have partnered together to bring the Pawnee community a mobile food pantry once a month. Last Wednesday we hosted our first Pawnee Community Mobile Food Pantry and it was a huge success! The food pantry will be available every 2nd Wednesday of the month between 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. in the back parking lot of the school. Our next mobile food pantry is scheduled for Dec. 11th.

post_text:
At my college graduation party, my parents handed me a check to start my life.

Instead of paying for private schools, they saved the tuition money for 12 years.

The education I got from Pawnee ISD fully prepared me for high school.

My teachers were state-certified, and the curriculum met stringent standards.

I learned invaluable people skills in a real-world setting of diverse students.

A public education earned acceptance offers for me from choice colleges.

Imagine - instead of leaving school with debt, your child could buy a house, start a business, or invest and retire early.

Pawnee ISD has a quality, tuition-free public education waiting for your child.

I was nervous about leaving my Pawnee middle school family.

I was picturing a new building, new teachers, and taller kids in the school halls...

The Pawnee school counselor hooked me up with some great people...

...and let me know about high school events I could attend.

Now, I‚Äôm not starting cold; I already know people and how to find my classes.

I‚Äôll get fist-bumps in the hallway instead of getting bumped against the lockers.

Pawnee ISD counselors help 8th-graders transition to high school...

...so their parents can relax, too.

Pawnee ISD individual planning gets 8th graders ‚Äúfuture-ready‚Äù!

I can‚Äôt keep up with the techie terms my kids are throwing around...

Our two boys are into coding, game design, and web development!

But I do worry about their safety in their online world‚Ä¶

...where comments are permanent and ‚Äúlikes‚Äù seem so transient.

New tech is exciting, but we need to teach our kids how to use it wisely.

At Pawnee ISD, we implement guidelines from CommonSenseMedia.org.

We promote 21st-century skills while teaching kids how to stay safe online.

And we make sure they know how to be a good ‚Äòdigital citizen‚Äô toward others.

Find tech education for student safety at Pawnee ISD.
